						<summary>

						<p>Slab on the plat form out side the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to about the 8th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Incomplete. It states that Kōki made a raid on Balavarmapāgu and died in the battle, while Saṁgrāmacheruvu was ruling over Koṟṟapaṟu.</p>						

						</summary>
